President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. 

Dereth Glance is being nominated as Commissioner of the International Joint Commission at the Department of State. She currently works as the Executive Program Director for Citizens Campaign for the Environment and has experience in environmental advocacy.

Rich Moy is also being nominated as Commissioner of the International Joint Commission at the Department of State. He is currently a Senior Fellow at the Center of Natural Resources and Environmental Policy and has worked on water policy and management issues.

Daniel B. Shapiro is being nominated as Ambassador to Israel at the Department of State. He currently serves as Senior Director for the Middle East and North Africa on the National Security Staff at the White House.

Ben S. Bernanke is being nominated as U.S. Alternate Governor to the International Monetary Fund in addition to his role as Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System.

Christopher B. Howard is being nominated as a Member of the National Security Education Board. He currently serves as the President of Hampden-Sydney College and has a background in leadership and strategic initiatives.

President Obama believes that these individuals will bring valuable experience and dedication to their new roles.